(7533,125053,'A viral infection of the brain caused by a member of the CALIFORNIA GROUP VIRUSES, transmitted to humans by the mosquito AEDES triseriatus. The majority of cases are caused by the LA CROSSE VIRUS. This condition is endemic to the midwestern United States and primarily affects children between 5-10 years of age. Clinical manifestations include FEVER, VOMITING, HEADACHE, and abdominal pain followed by SEIZURES, altered mentation, and focal neurologic deficits. (From Joynt, Clinical Neurology, 1996, Ch26, p13)','en',1,'2007-10-18 04:28:24',1,NULL,'7533FFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF'),
