(9055,129498,'A large, widely distributed genus of ticks consisting of approximately 245 species. Many infest man and other mammals and several are vectors of diseases such as LYME DISEASE, tick-borne encephalitis (ENCEPHALITIS, TICK-BORNE), and KYASANUR FOREST DISEASE.','en',1,'2007-10-18 04:28:24',1,NULL,'9055FFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF'),
