(9209,130335,'Vegetative state refers to the neurocognitive status of individuals with severe brain damage, in whom physiologic functions (sleep-wake cycles, autonomic control, and breathing) persist, but awareness (including all cognitive function and emotion) is abolished. A vegetative state may be transient, persistent, or permanent. A wide variety of diffuse insults to the brain may result in this condition including trauma (BRAIN INJURIES); hypoxia (HYPOXIA, BRAIN); CEREBROVASCULAR DISORDERS; CENTRAL NERVOUS SYSTEM INFECTIONS; BRAIN NEOPLASMS; toxins; METABOLIC DISEASES; and NEURODEGENERATIVE DISORDERS. (From Lancet 1998 Jun 13;351(9118):1763-7)','en',1,'2007-10-18 04:28:24',1,NULL,'9209FFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF'),
